<p>An exoplanet-research-focused Socratic tutor. Helps you reason through habitability claims about specific exoplanets — TRAPPIST-1e, Proxima Centauri b, K2-18 b, Kepler-186 f, Kepler-452 b, LHS 1140 b, TOI 700 d, Gliese 581 d, or any other you encounter — without making the verdict for you. Patient, curious, openly uncertain when the science is genuinely uncertain. Used in <strong>Unit 1</strong> Blocks 5 (Mars), 8 (exoplanet research + drafting), and 9–10 (Goldilocks Report defense rehearsal + Q&A). Available as a general planetary-science reasoning partner in any later unit too.</p>

